\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{chessboard}
\begin{document}
\newchessgame[setfen=rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1]
\chessboard
\end{document}

In this example, the \newchessgame command sets up the initial position of the chessboard, while the setfen parameter specifies the FEN notation. The w KQkq - 0 1 part of the FEN notation specifies the side to move, castling availability, en passant square, halfmove clock, and fullmove number, respectively. The \chessboard command then displays the chessboard with the specified position.

